# Raspberry Pi 5 — Production Deployment Configuration

**Version:** 1.0.0
**Date:** 2026-04-24
**Status:** Verified Working
**Platform:** Raspberry Pi 5, Debian GNU/Linux 13 (Trixie), aarch64
**Goal:** Native (no Docker) production server at `https://woosoo.local` serving 15 Android tablets

---

## Architecture Overview

```
Internet / LAN
      │
      ▼
[Tablet / Dev Machine]
  DNS → 192.168.100.42 (Pi dnsmasq)
      │
      ▼ HTTPS :443
[nginx — /etc/nginx/sites-available/woosoo]
      │
      ├── /app/*  ──────────────────────► [Reverb WebSocket :8080]  (supervisor)
      │
      ├── /api /admin /sanctum            [PHP-FPM unix socket]
      │   /broadcasting /up               fastcgi → /srv/woosoo/nexus/public/index.php
      │   /horizon /pulse ──────────────►
      │
      ├── /setup  /ca.crt ─────────────► /srv/woosoo/setup/  (static, HTTP only)
      │
      └── /* ──────────────────────────► /srv/woosoo/pwa/  (Nuxt static SPA)

[MariaDB :3306]  ◄─── woosoo-nexus (local)
[Krypton MySQL :3308]  ◄─── woosoo-nexus (remote, Windows machine)
[Redis :6379]  ◄─── Horizon queues, Pulse, session, cache
```

---

## Fixed vs Dynamic Values

| Value | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `woosoo.local` | **FIXED** | Domain used everywhere — TLS cert, nginx, .env, PWA build |
| `192.168.100.42` | **DYNAMIC** | Pi's LAN IP — changes per network (see §Network Change) |
| Krypton IP | **DYNAMIC** | Windows machine IP — changes per network |
| `REVERB_APP_KEY` / `REVERB_APP_SECRET` | **FIXED** | Generated once, never rotate unless security incident |
| `APP_KEY` | **FIXED** | Generated once — rotating invalidates all sessions/cookies |
| `DB_PASSWORD` | **FIXED** | Change only intentionally |
| `NUXT_PUBLIC_REVERB_APP_KEY` | **FIXED** | Must match `REVERB_APP_KEY` — baked into PWA build |

