## Step-by-Step Deployment Guide

### Phase 1 — OS & System Packages

**[MANDATORY] Install required packages:**
```bash
sudo apt install -y \
  php8.4-fpm php8.4-mysql php8.4-redis php8.4-mbstring \
  php8.4-bcmath php8.4-gd php8.4-zip php8.4-xml php8.4-curl \
  php8.4-intl php8.4-sqlite3 php8.4-opcache \
  nginx mariadb-server redis-server supervisor \
  nodejs npm git curl unzip \
  dnsmasq libnss3-tools
```

**[MANDATORY] Install Composer:**
```bash
curl -sS https://getcomposer.org/installer | sudo php -- --install-dir=/usr/local/bin --filename=composer
```

**[MANDATORY] Install mkcert (ARM64):**
```bash
curl -Lo mkcert https://github.com/FiloSottile/mkcert/releases/latest/download/mkcert-v1.4.4-linux-arm64
chmod +x mkcert && sudo mv mkcert /usr/local/bin/
```

> PHP 8.4 is the only version available on Debian Trixie. `pcntl` is built-in to CLI — no separate package needed.

---

### Phase 2 — Static IP (NetworkManager / WiFi)

> Pi uses WiFi at both home and restaurant. Static IP prevents DNS mismatch.

**[DYNAMIC — update per network]**

```bash
# Check connection name first — do not assume "preconfigured"
nmcli connection show
# On this Pi the WiFi connection is: "netplan-wlan0-blk 12 lt 31_2.4G"

# Set static IP (replace values for each network)
sudo nmcli con mod "netplan-wlan0-blk 12 lt 31_2.4G" \
  ipv4.addresses 192.168.100.42/24 \
  ipv4.gateway 192.168.100.1 \
  ipv4.dns 127.0.0.1 \
  ipv4.method manual
sudo nmcli con up "netplan-wlan0-blk 12 lt 31_2.4G"
```

> `ipv4.dns 127.0.0.1` — Pi resolves DNS through its own dnsmasq.
> `"preconfigured"` is the default WiFi connection name on Pi OS. Verify with `nmcli connection show`.

---

### Phase 3 — dnsmasq (LAN DNS)

**[MANDATORY — update krypton.local IP per network]**

File: `/etc/dnsmasq.conf`
```
address=/woosoo.local/192.168.100.42     # DYNAMIC — Pi's IP on current network
address=/krypton.local/192.168.100.7     # DYNAMIC — Krypton Windows machine IP
listen-address=127.0.0.1,192.168.100.42  # DYNAMIC — must include Pi's current IP
bind-interfaces
cache-size=150
local=/local/                             # MANDATORY — prevents avahi from intercepting .local
server=1.1.1.1                            # internet DNS fallback
server=8.8.8.8
```

**[MANDATORY] Fix avahi conflict** — avahi intercepts `.local` mDNS before dnsmasq.
Edit `/etc/nsswitch.conf`:
```
hosts: files dns mdns4
```
> DNS must come before mdns4. Default Debian order has mdns4_minimal before dns which breaks dnsmasq .local resolution.

```bash
sudo systemctl enable dnsmasq && sudo systemctl restart dnsmasq
```

