### Phase 4 — TLS Certificate (mkcert)

**[MANDATORY — one-time, valid until cert expiry ~2 years]**

```bash
mkcert -install
mkcert woosoo.local "*.woosoo.local"

sudo mkdir -p /srv/woosoo/certs
sudo mv woosoo.local+1.pem /srv/woosoo/certs/woosoo.local.pem
sudo mv woosoo.local+1-key.pem /srv/woosoo/certs/woosoo.local-key.pem
sudo chown www-data:www-data /srv/woosoo/certs/woosoo.local*.pem
sudo chmod 640 /srv/woosoo/certs/woosoo.local-key.pem

# Copy CA cert for tablet onboarding
sudo mkdir -p /srv/woosoo/setup
sudo cp ~/.local/share/mkcert/rootCA.pem /srv/woosoo/setup/ca.crt
```

> Each client device (tablet, dev machine) must install this CA cert once to trust `https://woosoo.local`.

