### Phase 10.5 — Automated MariaDB Backups

**[MANDATORY]** Nightly backups must be an actual scheduled job, not just a directory convention.

```bash
sudo mkdir -p /srv/woosoo/backups
sudo chown root:root /srv/woosoo/backups
sudo chmod 750 /srv/woosoo/backups
```

File: `/usr/local/bin/woosoo-backup.sh`

```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

timestamp="$(date +%F-%H%M%S)"
backup_dir="/srv/woosoo/backups"
backup_file="${backup_dir}/woosoo-${timestamp}.sql.gz"

mysqldump --single-transaction --quick -u woosoo -p'YOUR_DB_PASSWORD' woosoo \
    | gzip > "${backup_file}"

find "${backup_dir}" -type f -name 'woosoo-*.sql.gz' -mtime +7 -delete
```

```bash
sudo chmod 700 /usr/local/bin/woosoo-backup.sh
```

Cron entry (`sudo crontab -e`):

```cron
0 3 * * * /usr/local/bin/woosoo-backup.sh >> /var/log/woosoo/backup.log 2>&1
```

Minimum verification after enabling:

```bash
sudo run-parts --test /etc/cron.daily
sudo /usr/local/bin/woosoo-backup.sh
ls -lh /srv/woosoo/backups/
tail -n 20 /var/log/woosoo/backup.log
```

Restore rehearsal (run before go-live week and after any backup changes):

```bash
gunzip -c /srv/woosoo/backups/woosoo-<timestamp>.sql.gz | mysql -u woosoo -p woosoo
```

