### Phase 11 — PWA Deployment (tablet-ordering-pwa)

**[MANDATORY — rebuild whenever REVERB_APP_KEY changes or PWA code updates]**

Build is done on the Pi. Reverb key and host are **baked at build time**.

```bash
# Clone as current user (NOT sudo — avoids node_modules permission error)
cd /tmp && git clone https://github.com/tech-artificer/tablet-ordering-pwa.git pwa-build
cd /tmp/pwa-build

# Read key from production .env
REVERB_KEY=$(sudo grep '^REVERB_APP_KEY=' /etc/woosoo/.env | cut -d= -f2)

npm ci

NODE_ENV=production \
NUXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=/api \
NUXT_PUBLIC_REVERB_APP_KEY=$REVERB_KEY \
NUXT_PUBLIC_REVERB_HOST= \
NUXT_PUBLIC_REVERB_PORT=443 \
NUXT_PUBLIC_REVERB_SCHEME=https \
NUXT_PUBLIC_REVERB_PATH=/app \
npx --yes nuxi generate

sudo rm -rf /srv/woosoo/pwa/*
sudo cp -r .output/public/* /srv/woosoo/pwa/
sudo chown -R www-data:www-data /srv/woosoo/pwa/
cd ~ && rm -rf /tmp/pwa-build
```

> `NUXT_PUBLIC_REVERB_HOST=` (empty) — means the PWA uses the current browser hostname (`woosoo.local`). **Do not set this to an IP address.**
>
> This fallback is implemented in `tablet-ordering-pwa/utils/reverbSocketConfig.ts` and regression-covered by `tablet-ordering-pwa/tests/reverb-socket-config.spec.ts`.

