## Network Change Procedure

**When moving Pi to a different WiFi network (e.g., home → restaurant):**

### Step 1 — SSH in (always works via avahi mDNS)
```bash
ssh woosoo@woosoo-server.local
```

### Step 2 — Find new IP
```bash
hostname -I
```

### Step 3 — Update static IP
```bash
# WiFi connection name on this Pi: "netplan-wlan0-blk 12 lt 31_2.4G"
sudo nmcli con mod "netplan-wlan0-blk 12 lt 31_2.4G" \
  ipv4.addresses <NEW_IP>/24 \
  ipv4.gateway <NEW_GATEWAY> \
  ipv4.dns 127.0.0.1 \
  ipv4.method manual
sudo nmcli con up "netplan-wlan0-blk 12 lt 31_2.4G"
```

### Step 4 — Update dnsmasq
```bash
sudo nano /etc/dnsmasq.conf
# Update these two lines:
#   address=/woosoo.local/<NEW_PI_IP>
#   address=/krypton.local/<NEW_KRYPTON_IP>
#   listen-address=127.0.0.1,<NEW_PI_IP>
sudo systemctl restart dnsmasq
```

### Step 5 — Tell tablets new DNS
Each tablet WiFi setting: set DNS to `<NEW_PI_IP>`.

> TLS cert covers `woosoo.local` domain — no cert change needed when IP changes.
> App URLs never use IP directly — all traffic goes through `woosoo.local`.

