## Key Architectural Decisions

| Decision | Reason |
|---|---|
| No Docker — native install | Pi 5 has limited RAM; no overhead |
| nginx → PHP-FPM socket directly | No internal nginx layer needed (Docker pattern only) |
| Reverb internal HTTP `:8080`, public HTTPS `:443` | nginx terminates TLS; Reverb only handles WS frames |
| Pusher protocol path `/app/{key}` — NOT `/reverb` | Laravel Reverb uses Pusher-compatible paths |
| dnsmasq on Pi for LAN DNS | All 15 tablets + print-bridge resolve `woosoo.local` via Pi |
| `local=/local/` in dnsmasq | Prevents avahi-daemon intercepting `.local` queries |
| mkcert local CA | Self-signed HTTPS without browser warnings after CA install |
| `NUXT_PUBLIC_REVERB_HOST=` (empty) | PWA uses browser hostname — works correctly on `woosoo.local` |
| `config:cache` always active in production | Required for performance; means `env()` returns null in app code — use `config()` instead |

